tap

Class TAPExecutionReport

  • java.lang.Object
    • tap.TAPExecutionReport

  • public class TAPExecutionReport
extends java.lang.Object

    Report the execution (including the parsing and the output writing) of an ADQL query. It gives information on the job parameters, the job ID, whether it is a synchronous task or not, times of each execution step (uploading, parsing, executing and writing), the resulting columns and the success or not of the execution.

    This report is completely filled by ADQLExecutor, and aims to be used/read only at the end of the job or when it is definitely finished.

    Version:
    2.0 (04/2015)
    Author:
    Grégory Mantelet (CDS;ARI)

      • getIndexDuration

        protected int getIndexDuration(ExecutionProgression tapProgression)

        Map the execution progression with an index inside the durations array.

        Warning: for the moment, only ExecutionProgression.UPLOADING, ExecutionProgression.PARSING, ExecutionProgression.EXECUTING_ADQL and ExecutionProgression.WRITING_RESULT are managed.

        Parameters:
        tapProgression - Execution progression.
        Returns:
        Index in the array durations, or -1 if the given execution progression is not managed.
